The name 
<taxonomicName id="64BE77CB3C55A6F7EF1A8BBD2EA73F69" authorityName="Vujic, Likov &amp; Radenkovic" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="trianguloculus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trianguloculus">
<emphasis id="ECC336F82B655E860D3FDADC993270DA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">trianguloculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
derives from the Latin adjective 
<emphasis id="915D0C432F67FB8D2E5CBE0B6D96D2A8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">triangulus</emphasis>
(triangular) and Latin noun 
<emphasis id="0AF4ACBF6417F489907997B91CBCC480" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">loculus</emphasis>
(spot) and describes the distinctive triangular silver pollinose fasciae on the abdomen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="92D22384689F164A044E41E3A3091622" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="C3B388202920E53F5AAB54A187A7B83B" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2247AF02A8BDDE3B3F14046120841B86" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
<taxonomicName id="006291467CC761C2F1F8EFDA6E275217" authorityName="Vujic, Likov &amp; Radenkovic" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Merodon trianguloculus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trianguloculus">
<emphasis id="6B1108E027ED2E305393E7C9A3F8CA2B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Merodon trianguloculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. was recorded only in Turkmenistan (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E4B324879E09829242EB46C810491CE9" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Distribution map of Merodon serrulatus species group." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377368" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8594C1923D44E6976A910BC19ACE729F" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="663FA1BC58F1084D3F222495757E1041" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F3BFCE4C9F10B06D4D28C7ECFCC75B5E" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Preferred environment: open areas extending to the forest zone; unimproved grassland; adults resting on the stones and in flight between grasses at the top of Dushak Mountain. Flowers visited: no data. Flight period: May-June.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
